captions.text:
My name is Charly Iacono.
I have been practicing freestyle football for seven years.
I am the four time Argentinean champion.
Last year I qualified among the top 16 in Italy.

In my first battle, I lost against a guy from Belgium. 
I did the best I could, and I had more tricks to do.
It was a sad and tough moment.
Now I must train harder than ever to compete in Tokyo.

We are at Spacy, let's hear a loud applause!
Introducing, Ariel Ortega!
The truth is that its very difficult but you have to choose.
There are many hours of training and patience.
There is a higher level this year too.
I would really like to win so my training pays off.
This is the last battle of these quarterfinals.
A round of applause for the two finalists! Charly y Gonzalo
My expectations for now, of course, is to win the title for the fifth time.
One of these two will represent Argentina in the final in Tokyo

title: Freestyle Football in Argentina - Red Bull Street Style 2013
